William R. Smith (Mormon)

Jesse N. Smith

Portrait of Ira Eldredge with his three wives: Nancy Black Eldredge, Hannah Mariah Savage Eldredge, and Helvig Marie Andersen Eldredge. Ira was bishop of the Sugar House ward at the time the image was taken.

Robert T. Burton - A black and white photo of a man with a long beard

Angus M. Cannon - A black and white photo of a man with a mustache

Photo of Charles Ora Card, the founder of the town of Cardston, Alberta, the first Mormon settlement in Canada. He has been referred to as "Canada's Brigham Young".

Samuel Claridge - A black and white photo of a man with a beard

Photo of Samuel Claridge a prominent early settler of the Muddy River Valley in Nevada and also Thatcher, Arizona.

Joseph L. Heywood - A black and white photo of a man with a long beard

Photo of Joseph L. Heywood, a local leader of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints (LDS Church) in the 19th century, and the founder of Nephi, Utah.
